<br>
After a few days with this skill, it is obvious that the designers intent for this skill (aside from the really nifty CR implications) is to cater to raiding...particularly the fact that this skill replaces our discipline nimble as the method for controlling aggro fuck ups.  What is so important about that, you may ask?  <br>
<br>
Well, in the old days (have to chuckle at that since I'm hella new school) rogues would go along happily backstabbing and evading like the merry little folk they are, and when the tank died, or they screwed up their aggro on a mob that was hitting too hard for them to tank succesfully, they used nimble.  That was all well and good, and they could go merrily on their way backstabbing and evading after aggro was controlled again.  The downside? no duelist on that fight, or for 30 minutes.<br>
<br>
With escape, rogues can change their strategy slightly on high end mobs.  (High end does not mean the Emperor...I'm taking it to mean anything that requries a CH rotation).  Now, they can  afford to get aggro and still use duelist, wheras before they could not.  What does this mean?  Well, it means rogues have a serious upgrade in their ability to do damage, because they often DO get aggro if an MT goes down unexpectedly (sometimes rampage / oh shit tanks can prevent this by being sent in before the rest of the raid...sometimes) they can STILL use their most damaging discipline, which can give quite and edge to a tough fight.<br>
<br>
So my suggestion for improvement?  Lower the fucking timer.  72 minutes is more than the refresh time of TWO nimbles.  In fact, its about halfway through the refresh time of the third.  I don't mind it being down for two discs, actually because Manaburn and mass group buff have similar down times, but to have it repop in the middle of a disc refreshing isn't the best idea in the world.  Nimble was meant to be used in place of a disc, but I believe it is also mean to be used WITH a disc.  In raid situations the best possible combination would be Escape + duelist, in aggro transfers nimble + escape, in CRing nimble + escape.  So my suggestion is to please lower the refresh timer so that it refreshes WITH but not BEFORE the second discipline.<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=94771">Soulstone Elwyn</a>, lvl 60 Proctologist of <a href="http://www.pedworld.com/lod">LoD</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/usoulstoneelwyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soulstone Elwyn</A> at: 6/12/02 1:22:39 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/ubladestain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bladestain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/17/02 7:02:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumrogue.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=220.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ideas to improve and or replace rogue class AA.</span><hr size=1> I would like to see more poison components dropped off of higher level mobs or components that are not a bitch to find or obtain (not counting spider Ven sacks, LOL).  <br>
